WEBVTT

00:00:02.440 --> 00:00:04.237
- <i>Previously on</i> The O. C:
- You drink a lot?

00:00:04.400 --> 00:00:06.038
I guess. I mean, what's a lot?

00:00:06.240 --> 00:00:08.800
Have you ever had so much to drink
that you blacked out?

00:00:08.960 --> 00:00:12.316
How much is the Land Trust
offering me for Balboa Heights?

00:00:12.480 --> 00:00:14.596
That's it?
That's your whole dog-and-pony show?

00:00:14.800 --> 00:00:16.677
- What are you doing Saturday?
- What are you doing Saturday?

00:00:16.840 --> 00:00:20.230
- I have a date with Summer.
- What are you doing Friday night?

00:00:28.720 --> 00:00:30.631
So, what's it gonna be, huh?

00:00:30.800 --> 00:00:34.873
You want your menorah or
a candy cane? Christmas or Hanukkah?

00:00:37.400 --> 00:00:40.915
Don't worry about it, buddy, because
in this house, you don't have to choose.

00:00:41.120 --> 00:00:45.159
Allow me to introduce you
to a little something I like to call...

00:00:45.640 --> 00:00:47.710
...Chrismukkah.
- Chrismukkah?

00:00:47.880 --> 00:00:50.110
That's right.
The new holiday sweeping the nation.

00:00:50.280 --> 00:00:52.430
- Hey, fellas, we got the tree.
- Hey.

00:00:52.600 --> 00:00:55.558
- Or at least the living room.
- Guys, a little help.

00:00:55.720 --> 00:00:58.951
I saved a spot for you right there.
Put your muscle into it.

00:00:59.120 --> 00:01:01.315
Excellent. To the right a little.
Don't hurt it.

00:01:01.480 --> 00:01:03.357
Those needles are brittle.
That's perfect.

00:01:03.560 --> 00:01:07.917
You guys, you guys. A-plus. A-plus.
I love the holidays. I love them all.

00:01:08.080 --> 00:01:10.992
- We didn't really know how to raise Seth.
- So I raised myself.

00:01:11.160 --> 00:01:14.197
In doing so, I created the greatest
superholiday known to mankind...

00:01:14.360 --> 00:01:18.069
...drawing on the best that Christianity
and Judaism have to offer.

00:01:18.560 --> 00:01:19.879
And you call it Chrismukkah?

00:01:20.520 --> 00:01:24.149
Just hearing you say it makes me feel
all festive. Allow me to elaborate.

00:01:24.320 --> 00:01:28.233
You see, for my father here, a poor,
struggling Jew growing up in the Bronx...

00:01:28.440 --> 00:01:30.158
...Christmas meant
Chinese food and a movie.

00:01:30.320 --> 00:01:32.356
For my mom here,
Waspy McWasp...

00:01:32.520 --> 00:01:35.034
...well, it meant a tree,
stockings and all the trimmings.

00:01:35.200 --> 00:01:36.872
- Isn't that right?
- We're very proud.

00:01:37.040 --> 00:01:38.268
- I'm not a Wasp.
- Sure.

00:01:38.440 --> 00:01:42.228
Highlights include eight days of presents
followed by one of many presents.

00:01:42.400 --> 00:01:44.038
So, what do you think?

00:01:44.760 --> 00:01:47.877
- Sounds great for you guys.
- For you too.

00:01:48.040 --> 00:01:50.952
Hey, dip a toe in the Chrismukkah pool.
There's room for all of us.

00:01:51.120 --> 00:01:54.317
Isn't there an Atwood family tradition
you'd like to incorporate...

00:01:54.480 --> 00:01:56.630
...into Seth's ��ber-holiday?
- Yeah.

00:01:57.360 --> 00:02:00.193
Atwood and holidays
is not a good combination.

00:02:00.360 --> 00:02:03.591
- What did you guys do?
- No, seriously, thanks, but...

00:02:03.760 --> 00:02:05.796
Come on, man,
there's got to be something.

00:02:06.600 --> 00:02:09.512
My holiday memories pretty much
consist of my mom drunk...

00:02:09.680 --> 00:02:11.398
...and me getting my ass kicked.

00:02:13.600 --> 00:02:16.034
Well, this year will be entirely different.

00:02:16.200 --> 00:02:18.760
New memories. It'll be great.

00:02:20.440 --> 00:02:22.396
Yeah. Well, I'll do
whatever you want me to.

00:02:22.560 --> 00:02:24.676
That's the spirit. Come here.

00:02:28.720 --> 00:02:31.280
- <i>Oy</i> humbug.
- It's a big holiday for anyone.

00:02:31.440 --> 00:02:34.432
Yeah, I'm still wrapping my head
around it. Give him some time.

00:02:34.600 --> 00:02:36.909
Why don't we trim the tree?

00:02:37.080 --> 00:02:41.039
You know what, you guys? Soon Ryan
will learn the magic of Chrismukkah.

00:02:41.200 --> 00:02:44.476
Worry not. I will convert him.

00:03:25.760 --> 00:03:28.797
I was gone five minutes.
How did this turn into Santa's workshop?

00:03:28.960 --> 00:03:32.077
I see someone took down the wreath
I hung on the door.

00:03:32.240 --> 00:03:33.878
It fell. What are you wrapping?

00:03:34.040 --> 00:03:37.316
Two Seth Cohen starter packs. We got
Death Cab, Bright Eyes, The Shins...

00:03:37.480 --> 00:03:39.038
...<i>Kavalier & Clay</i> and <i>Goonies.</i>

00:03:39.200 --> 00:03:42.795
It's not just for kids, Ryan, it's not.
I don't care what they tell you.

00:03:42.960 --> 00:03:45.428
Summer and Anna
are gonna love them both equally.

00:03:45.600 --> 00:03:47.158
You're getting them the same thing?

00:03:47.320 --> 00:03:49.959
Yes, I am. Sometimes I'm so crafty,
I surprise myself.

00:03:50.120 --> 00:03:51.678
No good can come of this,
you know that.

00:03:51.840 --> 00:03:53.068
Nope, I don't.

00:03:53.240 --> 00:03:54.958
- You're gonna have to choose, man.
- Hey.

00:03:55.120 --> 00:03:58.271
Not on Chrismukkah, I don't. Okay?
There's no choosing in Chrismukkah.

00:03:58.440 --> 00:04:01.716
- Well, you didn't get me anything, right?
- No.

00:04:05.600 --> 00:04:07.636
Come on, man, lighten up.

00:04:08.040 --> 00:04:11.430
Okay, fine. Stay dark. Dark works too.

00:04:17.600 --> 00:04:20.239
- Oh, Ryan, what is your shoe size?
- Why?

00:04:20.720 --> 00:04:23.439
- No reason.
- Might that be a Chrismukkah list?

00:04:23.600 --> 00:04:25.192
- No. Why do you ask?
- Okay.

00:04:25.360 --> 00:04:28.033
- Let me just see it, then, real fast.
- It's work.

00:04:28.200 --> 00:04:31.078
- I love your work. It fascinates me.
- I thought you said no gifts.

00:04:31.240 --> 00:04:35.233
- Well, we did. As in, no gifts for us.
- All right. All right.

00:04:35.760 --> 00:04:37.432
Well, Chrismukkah's ruined.

00:04:38.120 --> 00:04:40.395
Don't even say it. It's unruinable.

00:04:40.560 --> 00:04:42.596
It's got twice the resistance
of any normal holiday.

00:04:42.760 --> 00:04:45.194
Your father refused our settlement offer.
He wants a trial.

00:04:45.360 --> 00:04:48.193
That's not what he said yesterday.
He said if you met his offer...

00:04:48.360 --> 00:04:50.749
As of this morning,
Scrooge wants to go to court...

00:04:50.920 --> 00:04:53.957
...which means I have to spend
the holidays preparing for trial.

00:04:54.120 --> 00:04:55.235
Because with Rachel
out...

00:04:55.400 --> 00:04:59.393
Chrismukkah is ruined. Sooner or later
we will get through a holiday around here.

00:04:59.560 --> 00:05:00.629
Stop it right now, okay?

00:05:00.800 --> 00:05:04.793
Don't give up on the miracle that is
Chrismukkah. What is happening to you...?

00:05:05.160 --> 00:05:09.676
You'll see. You'll see too.
You'll all see. You'll all see.

00:05:09.840 --> 00:05:12.115
- You're starting to scare me.
- I'm okay with that.

00:05:12.280 --> 00:05:16.432
Okey-dokey, here we go.
Which tie? What are you thinking?

00:05:16.600 --> 00:05:20.388
This one? All right? Or...

00:05:20.560 --> 00:05:24.030
- The second one, definitely.
- All right.

00:05:25.080 --> 00:05:28.231
- So you have a job interview today?
- It's just a meet and greet.

00:05:28.400 --> 00:05:31.790
But we gotta dress for success, right?

00:05:32.400 --> 00:05:34.630
Look, I'm working on it, kiddo.

00:05:34.800 --> 00:05:39.396
I'll find a job. I know there's a lot
of extra pressure on the holidays.

00:05:39.560 --> 00:05:41.152
There doesn't have to be pressure...

00:05:41.320 --> 00:05:45.233
...because there doesn't have to be
any holidays. Really.

00:05:45.400 --> 00:05:48.039
- What do you mean?
- We can skip Christmas. It's not like...

00:05:48.200 --> 00:05:52.239
...it's not gonna happen again next year,
and holidays just make people depressed.

00:05:53.480 --> 00:05:55.471
Are you? Depressed?

00:05:55.640 --> 00:05:58.359
You were supposed to go
to therapy after Mexico. We never...

00:05:58.520 --> 00:06:00.750
- I'm great. I'm just saying.
- Okay. Good.

00:06:00.920 --> 00:06:03.912
Because we're not skipping
Christmas. Come on.

00:06:04.080 --> 00:06:07.277
I'll find a job, we'll figure out
a way to make this whole thing work...

00:06:07.440 --> 00:06:09.908
...and we're gonna have
lots to celebrate about, okay?

00:06:10.080 --> 00:06:12.913
Come on. Skipping Christmas.

00:06:13.080 --> 00:06:16.038
- You sure about this tie?
- Yeah, definitely.

00:06:16.840 --> 00:06:18.956
- All right.
- You look great.

00:06:19.120 --> 00:06:21.588
Skipping Christmas.
What are you, the Grinch?

00:06:23.920 --> 00:06:26.480
So Summer and Anna
are both coming to this party?

00:06:26.640 --> 00:06:28.676
- But neither one's my date.
- They know that?

00:06:28.840 --> 00:06:30.671
Yeah, in theory they both know that.

00:06:31.000 --> 00:06:33.116
Come on, man, relax.
It's a big party, okay?

00:06:33.280 --> 00:06:35.635
You might be all doom and gloom,
but me? Check it out.

00:06:35.800 --> 00:06:38.473
I'm snowflakes. I'm latkes.
Chrismukkah is coming.

00:06:38.640 --> 00:06:40.517
And when Chrismukkah ends?

00:06:42.040 --> 00:06:44.554
- I hate when Chrismukkah ends.
- Cohen.

00:06:44.880 --> 00:06:47.838
Hi, Ryan. I wanted to know
what the deal was for tonight.

00:06:48.000 --> 00:06:50.150
If you were driving,
or should I pick you up?

00:06:50.360 --> 00:06:53.193
Hey, Seth. So, what time
are you thinking for tonight?

00:06:57.960 --> 00:07:00.190
- Hey, Summer.
- Hey, Anna.

00:07:00.600 --> 00:07:04.798
You guys. I was thinking that
we should all probably meet there.

00:07:04.960 --> 00:07:08.236
How about that? At whatever time
you choose, by whatever means.

00:07:09.920 --> 00:07:13.117
- Sounds great.
- Yeah. Perfect.

00:07:15.080 --> 00:07:17.594
You'd better pray
for a Chrismukkah miracle.

00:07:18.520 --> 00:07:20.875
I've got Jesus and Moses
on my side, man.

00:07:24.480 --> 00:07:27.552
Yeah, make sure all that
goes all the way around the bottom.

00:07:27.720 --> 00:07:32.032
Now, guys, the balls are the key
to the whole tree. They need to breathe.

00:07:34.480 --> 00:07:37.472
Hey, Kirsten, what do you think?

00:07:37.640 --> 00:07:40.518
- It's really something.
- You don't like it?

00:07:40.680 --> 00:07:45.595
It's not that. It's just that my mom used
to put the Christmas tree in the foyer.

00:07:45.760 --> 00:07:49.309
- It's just a tradition that we have.
- Yeah, Caleb told me.

00:07:49.480 --> 00:07:52.199
But then I thought, "You know,
the holidays are hard enough."

00:07:52.360 --> 00:07:54.794
Your father doesn't need
to be reminded of the past.

00:07:54.960 --> 00:07:56.916
Caleb needs to enjoy this Christmas.

00:07:57.080 --> 00:07:59.355
And did Caleb tell you
we need to borrow your office?

00:07:59.520 --> 00:08:02.956
We're doing the Santa thing for the kids,
and we need a holding area for the elves.

00:08:03.120 --> 00:08:04.439
What are you doing here?
Your father said...

00:08:04.600 --> 00:08:06.636
...you're working from home.
- He did?

00:08:06.800 --> 00:08:09.109
He's just
full of surprises.

00:08:10.240 --> 00:08:14.279
I changed my mind. If the Land Trust
can come up with $200 million...

00:08:14.440 --> 00:08:17.079
...then surely they can come up
with $300 million.

00:08:17.240 --> 00:08:18.753
I thought this was over.

00:08:18.920 --> 00:08:20.876
You can always get more blood
from the stone.

00:08:21.040 --> 00:08:23.235
But the stone is my husband.

00:08:23.400 --> 00:08:25.197
Let's spend the holidays working.

00:08:25.360 --> 00:08:28.989
- That sounds good. You have fun.
- What are you talking about?

00:08:29.160 --> 00:08:31.799
I'm gonna do something
that I haven't done in...

00:08:32.840 --> 00:08:33.955
...ever.

00:08:34.120 --> 00:08:37.795
- I'm taking Christmas vacation.
- Don't be ridiculous, Kiki.

00:08:37.960 --> 00:08:41.157
- You hate sitting around.
- Not as much as I hate fighting with you.

00:08:41.320 --> 00:08:43.595
So you spend two weeks
buried in legal documents.

00:08:43.760 --> 00:08:45.034
I'm gonna be wrapping gifts.

00:08:46.920 --> 00:08:51.072
- I hate Christmas.
- Well, Chrismukkah's not much better.

00:08:51.240 --> 00:08:54.118
You don't wanna know.
Holidays make what's bad even worse.

00:08:54.280 --> 00:08:55.713
I just wish my dad
would drop the act.

00:08:55.880 --> 00:08:58.314
I don't need it.
And I don't need Christmas.

00:08:58.560 --> 00:09:00.039
Who do you have to spend it with?

00:09:00.200 --> 00:09:02.760
Christmas Eve with my dad,
Christmas Day with my mom.

00:09:02.920 --> 00:09:05.753
Plus, she's making me go to a stupid
Newport Group party tonight.

00:09:05.920 --> 00:09:09.230
- The Cohens are going too, so...
- So at least we'll be miserable together.

00:09:09.640 --> 00:09:12.837
- Deal?
- Deal. So am I seeing you after school?

00:09:13.000 --> 00:09:16.436
I got some stuff to do,
some shopping. South Coast Plaza.

00:09:16.600 --> 00:09:19.558
You're going to South Coast Plaza?
Alone?

00:09:19.720 --> 00:09:20.835
I don't think
you're ready for that.

00:09:21.000 --> 00:09:23.230
You need a seasoned expert
to protect you.

00:09:23.920 --> 00:09:26.718
Well, you know someone?

00:10:04.320 --> 00:10:05.878
So no luck, huh?

00:10:06.040 --> 00:10:08.600
There's a 99-cent store down the street.

00:10:10.120 --> 00:10:13.157
I guess I can't really afford
this place anymore.

00:10:13.320 --> 00:10:15.038
Why did we come?

00:10:16.360 --> 00:10:19.796
I know it sounds stupid,
but I like it here.

00:10:19.960 --> 00:10:22.554
Everything is so perfect.

00:10:22.720 --> 00:10:24.551
You walk around feeling
like your problems...

00:10:24.720 --> 00:10:27.359
...can be solved by
the right nail polish...

00:10:27.520 --> 00:10:29.158
...or a new pair of shoes.

00:10:34.080 --> 00:10:36.594
Miss, I'm gonna have to ask
to see your purse.

00:10:36.760 --> 00:10:39.479
- Hey, what are you doing?
- I can't let you leave the premises.

00:10:39.640 --> 00:10:42.677
If you don't hand over your purse,
I'll have to call the police.

00:10:42.840 --> 00:10:44.193
Look, back off, all right?

00:10:44.360 --> 00:10:46.510
- Ryan, it's okay.
- No, it's not.

00:10:46.680 --> 00:10:48.398
Your purse. Now.

00:10:52.080 --> 00:10:54.230
What are you doing?

00:11:23.640 --> 00:11:25.312
What are you doing?
Working from home?

00:11:25.480 --> 00:11:27.550
- I'm on vacation.
- Yes. Clearly.

00:11:27.720 --> 00:11:31.315
- I find reviewing accounts to be relaxing.
- I hope that's a recessive gene.

00:11:31.520 --> 00:11:33.351
You should be so lucky.

00:11:33.520 --> 00:11:37.991
Look, I haven't taken a vacation
in a while, and I'm easing into it.

00:11:38.160 --> 00:11:40.879
- I don't judge. I only mock.
- That you get from your father.

00:11:41.040 --> 00:11:43.031
Oh, my God, they're coming in?

00:11:43.200 --> 00:11:46.829
Oh, the... I got you. What are those?

00:11:47.000 --> 00:11:50.072
They came for Ryan
from his mom and his brother.

00:11:51.000 --> 00:11:53.355
You know what he said
about the holidays?

00:11:53.520 --> 00:11:56.239
When he talks like that,
I have no idea what to say.

00:11:56.400 --> 00:11:59.153
Me neither. You just have
to be yourself.

00:11:59.320 --> 00:12:00.719
Yeah, because that
always works so well.

00:12:00.880 --> 00:12:03.838
Being a family is hard
under any circumstance.

00:12:04.000 --> 00:12:08.551
Creating a new one?
That's gotta feel weird sometimes.

00:12:08.720 --> 00:12:11.393
Feeling weird is
right in my wheelhouse.

00:12:14.280 --> 00:12:17.556
What is it? Is Grandpa going crazy
with the company credit card again?

00:12:17.760 --> 00:12:20.513
What is it this time? Hookers?
A little blow, perhaps?

00:12:20.680 --> 00:12:22.511
Grandpa likes to dance
with ye white lady?

00:12:22.680 --> 00:12:26.070
- What are you talking about?
- I don't know. What is it?

00:12:26.240 --> 00:12:27.593
It's... Hopefully, it's nothing.

00:12:27.760 --> 00:12:30.433
You should go get ready,
because we have to be there soon.

00:12:30.600 --> 00:12:32.079
I'll go put on my face.

00:12:41.960 --> 00:12:44.520
Hi. This is Kirsten Cohen
from the Newport Group.

00:12:44.680 --> 00:12:48.559
My father ordered a survey of
the Balboa Heights and I've lost my copy.

00:12:48.720 --> 00:12:53.589
I really need to see the document.
Is it possible for you to fax it over to me?

00:13:00.240 --> 00:13:02.993
- I cannot believe this. Marissa?
- Julie.

00:13:03.160 --> 00:13:06.197
Look, I have to host the most important
event of my career tonight.

00:13:06.360 --> 00:13:08.157
At least your priorities are in order.

00:13:08.320 --> 00:13:11.676
You know, it's amazing how these
calamities keep happening on your watch.

00:13:11.840 --> 00:13:13.910
Oh, so I'm to blame for this one too?

00:13:14.080 --> 00:13:15.957
- Where did she learn to steal?
- Stop it.

00:13:16.280 --> 00:13:19.829
I'm the one who stole, remember?
I'm the one to blame, not Dad.

00:13:20.000 --> 00:13:23.072
Look, we're lucky the store
is not pressing charges.

00:13:23.280 --> 00:13:26.238
Okay? Marissa and I were deciding
what an appropriate punishment...

00:13:26.400 --> 00:13:31.428
Oh, really? Well, way to rule with
the iron fist, Stalin, but it's not up to her.

00:13:31.600 --> 00:13:35.195
- No car, no allowance, no weekends.
- So I can stay home tonight?

00:13:35.360 --> 00:13:40.036
Starting tomorrow. I won't have my
party ruined by your little sticky fingers.

00:13:40.640 --> 00:13:46.033
Look, sweetie, I know that this time of
year makes everything bad seem worse.

00:13:46.200 --> 00:13:47.519
But why did you do this?

00:13:50.760 --> 00:13:53.228
I thought it would be...

00:13:53.720 --> 00:13:55.631
Look, I wasn't...

00:13:59.160 --> 00:14:00.149
It was stupid.

00:14:00.360 --> 00:14:02.157
I called the therapist
on the way over.

00:14:02.320 --> 00:14:04.276
- Mom.
- She's right, kiddo.

00:14:04.440 --> 00:14:06.476
Therapy was part of the deal
of you moving in.

00:14:06.640 --> 00:14:09.837
Okay, look, I've been doing
way better since Mexico.

00:14:10.000 --> 00:14:12.719
4.0 first quarter.
Charity League, social chair.

00:14:12.880 --> 00:14:16.270
I scheduled you an appointment
tomorrow with Dr. Milano. He's great.

00:14:16.560 --> 00:14:20.394
I'm sorry, but I can handle it.

00:14:20.560 --> 00:14:24.235
This. L... I won't do it again, I promise.

00:14:24.920 --> 00:14:27.753
Honey, I love you.

00:14:30.040 --> 00:14:31.155
But I don't believe you.

00:14:33.200 --> 00:14:35.156
You might actually find it helpful.

00:14:36.240 --> 00:14:38.515
Yeah. Whatever. I need to get ready.

00:14:38.680 --> 00:14:40.557
And, Mom, you have your
big party to throw.

00:14:40.720 --> 00:14:43.792
I'm sure you don't want to keep
Caleb waiting.

00:14:49.520 --> 00:14:51.351
Hey. What's up, man? You're back.

00:14:53.520 --> 00:14:57.035
So that's pretty cool, right?
Your mom and brother got you something.

00:14:57.200 --> 00:15:00.033
Yeah. Except now I have
a total of eight gifts to buy.

00:15:00.200 --> 00:15:01.519
I only saved enough for one.

00:15:01.680 --> 00:15:05.912
Ryan, that sort of reminds me
of the story of Hanukkah, dude.

00:15:06.080 --> 00:15:10.596
Check it out. The lamp... You know what?
I think you get the gist.

00:15:10.760 --> 00:15:14.389
- How was the mall?
- Weird.

00:15:15.200 --> 00:15:18.033
You've really painted a picture for me.
I feel like I was there.

00:15:18.200 --> 00:15:20.953
Marissa picked up a few things
without paying for them.

00:15:22.160 --> 00:15:24.469
- What? As in...
- Shoplifting.

00:15:24.760 --> 00:15:26.273
Yeah.

00:15:26.800 --> 00:15:29.155
- Yeah, that's weird.
- It's the time of year.

00:15:29.320 --> 00:15:31.788
And with everything that's going on
with her family...

00:15:31.960 --> 00:15:34.633
- Yeah, I'm sure it's gotta be hard for her.
- Yeah.

00:15:34.800 --> 00:15:38.998
I just wish there was something
I could do or say.

00:15:41.320 --> 00:15:42.389
Oh, I got you something.

00:15:42.560 --> 00:15:46.633
- No, no, no. We had an agreement.
- But this is different, this is a requirement.

00:15:46.800 --> 00:15:51.828
I know it's a bit minty, but, you know,
we all have one, so we just thought...

00:15:53.280 --> 00:15:54.793
No, that's cool.

00:15:54.960 --> 00:15:57.793
Well, good. Maybe it'll meet
a kinder fate than your wreath did.

00:15:57.960 --> 00:16:00.269
But, if not, we still
wanted you to have it.

00:16:00.440 --> 00:16:02.158
- Thanks.
- All right.

00:16:02.360 --> 00:16:03.588
I'm gonna go
make magic happen.

00:16:03.760 --> 00:16:06.672
I feel like my hair's
working for me tonight.

00:16:16.240 --> 00:16:18.708
I'm late. I know. I know.

00:16:19.840 --> 00:16:22.513
I'll hurry.
You're not gonna believe this...

00:16:22.680 --> 00:16:25.069
...but your father and I
reached a settlement today.

00:16:25.240 --> 00:16:28.277
He gouged me a little.
Well, you know, he gouged me a lot.

00:16:28.440 --> 00:16:33.275
- He asked you for more money?
- Just $250 million.

00:16:33.440 --> 00:16:34.509
But we closed the deal.

00:16:34.680 --> 00:16:37.717
- He claims that he did it because of you.
- Is that what he told you?

00:16:37.880 --> 00:16:40.474
It seems your vacation
really hit him hard.

00:16:40.640 --> 00:16:44.428
Because he says he wants
to spend the holidays as a family.

00:16:45.120 --> 00:16:48.874
You know, maybe...
Maybe he's changing.

00:16:49.040 --> 00:16:53.909
Or maybe he is a truly fantastic liar.
What's wrong?

00:16:59.800 --> 00:17:01.074
I found something today.

00:17:01.360 --> 00:17:05.069
And I don't know if I can give it to you,
but I don't know if I can't.

00:17:05.240 --> 00:17:09.677
- Okay, well...
- He's gonna know that I gave this to you.

00:17:09.840 --> 00:17:12.400
And he's gonna have
every right to fire me.

00:17:28.560 --> 00:17:30.152
You have got to be kidding me.

00:17:32.520 --> 00:17:33.873
This changes everything.

00:17:34.040 --> 00:17:37.919
And I'm gonna have to learn how to relax,
because I'm gonna have a lot of free time.

00:17:39.000 --> 00:17:43.278
- I'm sorry, honey.
- Not as sorry as he's gonna be.

00:17:44.840 --> 00:17:48.958
- You still wanna go to the party?
- I wouldn't miss it for the world.

00:18:05.080 --> 00:18:07.753
- Anna. Hey.
- Mistletoe.

00:18:08.640 --> 00:18:11.757
That's very festive of you.

00:18:11.920 --> 00:18:13.672
I thought we were meeting there.

00:18:13.840 --> 00:18:15.671
I was thinking maybe
we could go together.

00:18:15.880 --> 00:18:17.393
I would love to.
You know I would.

00:18:17.560 --> 00:18:19.357
But don't you think
that would violate...

00:18:19.520 --> 00:18:21.556
...our little Geneva Convention
of dating we have?

00:18:21.720 --> 00:18:23.790
Because I told Summer
I'd meet you both there.

00:18:23.960 --> 00:18:25.996
Well, how is Summer ever gonna know?

00:18:29.680 --> 00:18:32.752
- Mistletoe. What is she doing here?
- What are you doing here?

00:18:32.920 --> 00:18:35.229
- I thought we had a deal, Cohen.
- Which you violated.

00:18:35.400 --> 00:18:36.958
- As did you.
- She's got a point.

00:18:37.120 --> 00:18:40.237
- You're on her side?
- No. There are no sides, you guys.

00:18:40.400 --> 00:18:44.712
There's only rides. With my parents.
We'll all go together.

00:18:47.520 --> 00:18:49.511
- Fine.
- Fine.

00:19:01.960 --> 00:19:06.750
So I have a gift for you.
I'll give it to you later.

00:19:06.920 --> 00:19:12.278
I have a present for you too.
I'll also give it to you later.

00:19:12.440 --> 00:19:14.476
I can't wait.

00:19:14.640 --> 00:19:16.551
For either.

00:19:16.720 --> 00:19:18.312
For both.

00:19:18.960 --> 00:19:21.838
Seth, are you ready?
Come on, let's go.

00:19:22.720 --> 00:19:25.792
Hi, Summer. Anna.

00:19:25.960 --> 00:19:27.552
Ladies.

00:19:27.720 --> 00:19:29.312
Oh, this is gonna be some party.

00:19:31.920 --> 00:19:34.992
You know, maybe it's not
such a bad idea.

00:19:35.920 --> 00:19:37.717
What does that mean?

00:19:37.880 --> 00:19:39.871
It might be good
to have someone to talk to.

00:19:40.040 --> 00:19:43.430
- You're someone. I can't talk to you?
- You can talk to me, it's just...

00:19:43.600 --> 00:19:46.956
What? I need the help of a trained
professional because I stole a lipstick?

00:19:47.120 --> 00:19:50.874
- It's not about the lipstick.
- Then I guess I don't see what it's about.

00:19:51.760 --> 00:19:54.672
- You should do what you want.
- I will.

00:19:54.840 --> 00:19:58.037
If no one's making my parents
go to therapy, then no one's making me.

00:19:58.200 --> 00:20:01.351
You know, I'm the only
normal one in this family.

00:20:03.520 --> 00:20:05.033
Sorry.

00:20:06.880 --> 00:20:10.555
I think I left my wrap upstairs. Could you
grab it for me? I need to get my purse.

00:20:10.720 --> 00:20:12.517
Sure.

00:20:49.760 --> 00:20:51.876
Mushroom crescent?
Crab and brie phyllo?

00:20:52.040 --> 00:20:54.235
Come on, buddy.
Change it up a little bit.

00:20:54.400 --> 00:20:56.197
Enjoy the party.

00:20:56.640 --> 00:20:59.359
Come on, Seth. I'm going this way.

00:20:59.520 --> 00:21:01.590
I'm going this way.

00:21:01.760 --> 00:21:05.389
Oh, you guys are?
I'm gonna go look for Ryan. Excuse me.

00:21:07.600 --> 00:21:09.636
Kirsten, Sandy, welcome.

00:21:09.800 --> 00:21:11.233
- Kiki.
- Hey.

00:21:11.440 --> 00:21:14.034
Great to see you.
Did Sandman give you our good news?

00:21:14.360 --> 00:21:16.078
- He did.
- I need to follow up...

00:21:16.240 --> 00:21:17.832
...on some things with you,
if you don't mind...

00:21:18.000 --> 00:21:19.274
Come, Sanford, it's a party.

00:21:19.440 --> 00:21:22.512
Look back on your Berkeley days.
Maybe you can smoke the tree.

00:21:23.840 --> 00:21:25.876
Smoke the tree. Funny.

00:21:26.040 --> 00:21:27.996
I'm gonna nail him now.

00:21:28.880 --> 00:21:31.110
- So, what do you think?
- About?

00:21:31.280 --> 00:21:33.396
The party. You haven't said anything.
Like it?

00:21:33.560 --> 00:21:35.198
I mean, I know how you feel
about the tree...

00:21:35.360 --> 00:21:36.952
...but if you can get past that.

00:21:37.120 --> 00:21:38.838
- It's great.
- And what did Caleb think?

00:21:39.000 --> 00:21:42.834
- I mean, has he said anything to you?
- I haven't had a chance to talk to him.

00:21:43.040 --> 00:21:46.077
I just want this to be
a party that he'll never forget.

00:21:46.240 --> 00:21:48.595
I think you have a shot.

00:21:59.840 --> 00:22:01.910
- You okay?
- Yeah. Why?

00:22:02.480 --> 00:22:03.549
I don't know.

00:22:03.720 --> 00:22:05.438
Today's been kind of intense...

00:22:05.640 --> 00:22:08.234
...and I know you don't
really wanna be here.

00:22:08.400 --> 00:22:11.278
I wanna be where you are,
and you're here, so...

00:22:13.320 --> 00:22:17.074
Marissa.
Oh, you wore the Chanel. How pretty.

00:22:17.240 --> 00:22:19.754
Ryan. You haven't said hello to Caleb yet.

00:22:19.920 --> 00:22:22.912
He was talking to other people,
and I didn't want to interrupt.

00:22:23.080 --> 00:22:24.877
- He's ready now, so...
- I'm not.

00:22:25.040 --> 00:22:26.758
- Marissa.
- Mom.

00:22:26.920 --> 00:22:29.275
- You are a guest at this party.
- You made me come.

00:22:29.440 --> 00:22:32.352
- You're in enough trouble.
- Then I guess I've got nothing to lose.

00:22:32.520 --> 00:22:35.671
- This is the way it's gonna be?
- I don't know. I'll ask my shrink.

00:22:37.400 --> 00:22:39.994
You know what,
I'm gonna go to the bathroom.

00:22:41.280 --> 00:22:44.875
- I hate the holidays.
- Right there with you.

00:22:49.280 --> 00:22:50.918
Caleb. You have time to talk?

00:22:51.080 --> 00:22:53.389
- No.
- Come on, make some.

00:22:56.480 --> 00:22:59.040
- What is this?
- A geological survey of the Heights...

00:22:59.200 --> 00:23:02.590
...which you commissioned and somehow
failed to turn over to my office.

00:23:02.760 --> 00:23:04.512
- I've no time for this.
- I think you do.

00:23:04.680 --> 00:23:06.432
Allow me to summarize what you know.

00:23:06.600 --> 00:23:09.910
The Heights are seismologically unsound,
the whole area is uninsurable.

00:23:10.080 --> 00:23:12.958
- It's worthless.
- As is your theory.

00:23:13.120 --> 00:23:15.475
There's no way
you'd have gotten a building permit.

00:23:15.640 --> 00:23:17.596
- And you knew that.
- What do you want, Sandy?

00:23:17.760 --> 00:23:19.910
I wanna buy back the Heights.

00:23:20.080 --> 00:23:21.638
For a dollar.

00:23:23.160 --> 00:23:25.116
You cannot be serious.

00:23:27.160 --> 00:23:29.196
Merry Christmas.

00:23:32.000 --> 00:23:34.719
So are you ready for your present?

00:23:34.880 --> 00:23:38.190
Yeah, I'm ready. Hand me the keys.
I'll learn to drive stick eventually.

00:23:38.360 --> 00:23:40.430
Very funny, Seth.
Always have to ruin the mood.

00:23:40.600 --> 00:23:41.635
That's what I do.

00:23:42.640 --> 00:23:43.959
Ready?

00:23:51.880 --> 00:23:54.792
<i>The Adventures of Seth Cohen</i>
<i>and Captain Oats.</i>

00:23:54.960 --> 00:23:56.951
<i>Volume 1: "Confidence."</i>

00:23:57.120 --> 00:23:59.793
- You made this?
- No, I bought it on eBay.

00:23:59.960 --> 00:24:02.394
I can't believe you did this.
This is amazing.

00:24:03.480 --> 00:24:06.358
Hey, this Seth in the story
seems really handsome and awesome.

00:24:06.520 --> 00:24:10.638
- I guess I took some liberties.
- You dumbed him down a little bit.

00:24:19.640 --> 00:24:21.756
- This is fantastic.
- Thanks.

00:24:22.920 --> 00:24:26.390
- So how's Seth doing?
- He's fine, I think.

00:24:26.560 --> 00:24:29.757
It's hard to tell
with him sometimes. Why?

00:24:30.720 --> 00:24:34.030
Does he ever do things that sort of...

00:24:34.200 --> 00:24:37.272
...make you question yourself
as a parent?

00:24:38.680 --> 00:24:42.673
Well, there was the model home
and Tijuana...

00:24:42.840 --> 00:24:44.273
...and a thing with the Range Rover...

00:24:44.440 --> 00:24:47.034
...and an IMAX movie that
I didn't quite buy.

00:24:47.200 --> 00:24:51.034
But they're kids. I mean, they do stuff.
They get in trouble, right?

00:24:51.200 --> 00:24:54.078
Our parents would've had a heart attack
if they knew what we did.

00:24:54.240 --> 00:24:58.677
Come on, we were good kids.
We were. Weren't we?

00:24:58.840 --> 00:25:00.592
- We were good kids.
- Yeah.

00:25:00.760 --> 00:25:03.274
And we have good kids.

00:25:41.880 --> 00:25:44.155
Okay, hang on for a second.
What are we doing here?

00:25:44.320 --> 00:25:47.392
Because Anna went to get drinks.
She'll be back in, like, one second.

00:25:47.560 --> 00:25:49.551
- Come here.
- Why?

00:25:49.720 --> 00:25:51.153
- Just come here.
- Okay.

00:25:53.160 --> 00:25:54.434
Stay there.

00:26:02.920 --> 00:26:04.751
I hear you like comic books, Cohen.

00:26:05.320 --> 00:26:07.151
This is true.

00:26:11.080 --> 00:26:13.150
Merry Christmas.

00:26:22.080 --> 00:26:24.640
Good Lord, I think I'm gonna pass out.

00:26:26.360 --> 00:26:29.796
- You're not going anywhere.
- Okay.

00:26:35.800 --> 00:26:38.314
- Yes?
- What's this?

00:26:39.000 --> 00:26:40.797
That's Anna's present.
She made it for me.

00:26:41.280 --> 00:26:43.874
- She made it?
- Yeah.

00:26:44.280 --> 00:26:45.872
It's amazing.

00:26:46.040 --> 00:26:48.793
I know, but your present's amazing too.
It's really amazing.

00:26:50.200 --> 00:26:51.997
Hey, there you...

00:26:52.160 --> 00:26:53.593
...are.

00:26:54.360 --> 00:26:57.716
Hey, Anna, Summer was just
giving me her gift. It's cool.

00:26:57.880 --> 00:27:01.077
- You're Wonder Woman?
- Yeah. So?

00:27:01.280 --> 00:27:03.236
I mean, you look...

00:27:03.400 --> 00:27:05.152
...amazing.

00:27:05.320 --> 00:27:07.197
Is that my story?

00:27:08.600 --> 00:27:12.912
My God, I made you a comic book.
What am I, 8?

00:27:13.920 --> 00:27:15.273
Way to go, Wonder Whore.

00:27:15.440 --> 00:27:17.396
Hey, Wonder Woman's not
a whore, okay? Stop.

00:27:17.560 --> 00:27:19.835
- What are we doing?
- I don't know, this is nuts.

00:27:20.000 --> 00:27:21.592
Hold up, you guys, one second.

00:27:21.760 --> 00:27:24.672
Let's not have one speed bump
derail the whole train, okay?

00:27:24.840 --> 00:27:27.308
Let's not throw the baby out
with the bath water.

00:27:27.960 --> 00:27:29.791
- Let's make some more metaphors.
- Look...

00:27:29.960 --> 00:27:34.636
...I'm not into talking about, like,
feelings or whatever...

00:27:34.800 --> 00:27:35.949
...but I like you.

00:27:36.120 --> 00:27:38.350
Okay, and so does she.

00:27:40.160 --> 00:27:43.470
- Lf we don't put an end to this soon...
- Someone's gonna get hurt.

00:27:44.920 --> 00:27:46.114
You gotta choose, Cohen.

00:28:00.360 --> 00:28:02.112
Did you miss me?

00:28:02.480 --> 00:28:05.199
- Come on, let's dance.
- You know how I feel about dancing.

00:28:05.360 --> 00:28:07.999
You know how I don't care.
Come on, it's a party.

00:28:08.160 --> 00:28:09.912
Yeah, an office party.

00:28:10.080 --> 00:28:14.153
I thought you wanted to have fun.
Don't make me make you have fun.

00:28:15.640 --> 00:28:17.551
I'm guessing that's not eggnog.

00:28:17.720 --> 00:28:21.759
So what? Come on, if you don't wanna
dance we could just get out of here.

00:28:21.920 --> 00:28:26.436
- I didn't see you with a cocktail.
- Well, maybe I brought my own.

00:28:26.600 --> 00:28:28.272
Want some?

00:28:29.040 --> 00:28:30.393
What's going on with you today?

00:28:31.160 --> 00:28:34.038
- What's the big deal? You drink.
- Not alone in the bathroom.

00:28:34.200 --> 00:28:35.553
I'm just having fun.

00:28:35.720 --> 00:28:38.029
When I met you,
you were passed out in your driveway.

00:28:38.200 --> 00:28:40.509
Then it was an alley in Mexico. It's like...

00:28:40.680 --> 00:28:42.193
It's like my mom all over again.

00:28:42.480 --> 00:28:44.471
Shut up.

00:28:44.640 --> 00:28:46.835
- We're getting out of here.
- No, I am.

00:28:47.000 --> 00:28:48.513
- Enjoy the party.
- You can't drive.

00:28:48.680 --> 00:28:52.958
Get your hands off of me. I have enough
people in my life telling me what to do.

00:28:55.040 --> 00:28:56.837
See you.

00:29:08.520 --> 00:29:10.431
- Come on, let me drive.
- Get away from me.

00:29:10.680 --> 00:29:11.795
Hey.

00:29:11.960 --> 00:29:13.359
Hey.

00:29:13.920 --> 00:29:16.229
I'm fine.

00:29:34.680 --> 00:29:38.389
And so, effective immediately,
I'm transferring the title of the Heights...

00:29:38.560 --> 00:29:41.791
...to the Balboa Land Trust
for the very reasonable price...

00:29:41.960 --> 00:29:43.313
...of $ 1.

00:29:47.800 --> 00:29:51.475
And I couldn't have done it without
the help of my son-in-law, Sandy Cohen.

00:29:54.400 --> 00:29:57.915
Thanks, Cal. But I can't take credit
for this. You did this all on your own.

00:29:58.080 --> 00:30:01.629
To Caleb Nichol, the most generous
man in Newport Beach.

00:30:02.440 --> 00:30:04.590
Thanks.

00:30:09.480 --> 00:30:11.516
Happy Hanukkah, Sandy.

00:30:33.440 --> 00:30:35.032
- Great.
- What? You're driving.

00:30:35.200 --> 00:30:37.760
- Yeah, because you're drunk.
- I'm not...

00:30:39.120 --> 00:30:40.519
Fine.

00:30:45.320 --> 00:30:47.276
- Where is it?
- Come on, put it away.

00:30:47.440 --> 00:30:49.237
- I'm trying.
- I'm still on probation.

00:30:49.400 --> 00:30:51.550
I said, I'm trying.

00:30:57.920 --> 00:31:00.115
Of course this is happening.

00:31:02.960 --> 00:31:04.791
Oh, God.

00:31:18.800 --> 00:31:22.395
Happy holidays. License. Registration.

00:31:23.040 --> 00:31:25.031
You got a broken tail light,
you know that?

00:31:25.200 --> 00:31:26.872
It just happened. I'll get it fixed.

00:31:28.040 --> 00:31:30.759
- You kids haven't been drinking?
- No, sir.

00:31:34.800 --> 00:31:38.110
- Everything all right here, miss?
- Yeah, fine. Thanks.

00:31:40.320 --> 00:31:41.878
- Miss, would you...?
- <i>We got a 459...</i>

00:31:42.040 --> 00:31:43.758
<i>... at 1508 Cornwall Lane</i>
<i>in West Cliff.</i>

00:31:43.920 --> 00:31:46.036
<i>All cars in the area</i>
<i>please respond immediately.</i>

00:31:46.480 --> 00:31:48.277
Copy that.

00:31:48.440 --> 00:31:50.510
I've got a call I need to get to.

00:31:50.680 --> 00:31:54.514
I'm gonna let you go with just a warning
for that tail light. You get that fixed.

00:31:54.680 --> 00:31:56.477
- Drive straight home.
- Yes, sir.

00:32:22.200 --> 00:32:23.997
Stop, okay? You're scaring me.

00:32:24.160 --> 00:32:26.515
Good. You're scaring me.

00:32:31.440 --> 00:32:35.479
There's drinking, crying, cops.
Well, it must be Christmas.

00:32:51.800 --> 00:32:53.870
I left this behind.

00:32:54.880 --> 00:32:56.313
I am not doing it again.

00:32:58.720 --> 00:33:00.278
Okay.

00:33:09.000 --> 00:33:10.718
Okay.

00:33:26.680 --> 00:33:28.716
Well, the ladies laid down the law.
It's over.

00:33:28.880 --> 00:33:31.269
- What are you gonna do?
- I have no idea.

00:33:31.440 --> 00:33:34.750
I don't know. No female's
ever really offered me a choice.

00:33:34.920 --> 00:33:37.798
I really only know
how to handle rejection and ridicule.

00:33:37.960 --> 00:33:41.077
I have a really good handle on ridicule.
How was your night?

00:33:42.240 --> 00:33:46.074
Marissa got drunk, and we got pulled over
by the cops with an open bottle of vodka.

00:33:46.240 --> 00:33:48.959
Hey, that Marissa's really
making life interesting for you.

00:33:49.120 --> 00:33:51.953
- Yeah. We got in a fight.
- What about the cop?

00:33:52.120 --> 00:33:56.750
Got a radio call. Let us off
with a warning for a busted tail light.

00:33:56.920 --> 00:34:00.276
- Now you see why I hate Christmas.
- Hang on a second, Ryan.

00:34:00.440 --> 00:34:05.230
It seems to me that what we have here
is a Chrismukkah miracle.

00:34:05.400 --> 00:34:08.836
Thank you. Think about it for a second.
The old Ryan, what would've happened?

00:34:09.000 --> 00:34:12.675
He would've got busted. For sure. But
this time, you had Jesus working for you.

00:34:12.840 --> 00:34:15.149
And you had Moses.
Working together. The super team.

00:34:15.320 --> 00:34:18.676
Fighting for you, to keep you safe
and give you a second chance.

00:34:18.840 --> 00:34:20.592
Touched by an angel.

00:34:20.760 --> 00:34:24.639
That's nice. It's got a good ring to it.
I believe my faith has been restored.

00:34:25.400 --> 00:34:26.674
I should go get ready.

00:34:26.840 --> 00:34:29.513
- Anna will be here soon.
- What are you going to tell her?

00:34:29.680 --> 00:34:31.477
I'm sure the words will come.

00:34:32.120 --> 00:34:35.476
All right, I just think that...

00:34:35.640 --> 00:34:37.949
...considering everything...
Actually, wait, hang on.

00:34:38.120 --> 00:34:40.918
Let me actually try another approach.

00:34:41.080 --> 00:34:45.437
I think you're awesome,
and you're hilarious, and you're <i>caliente.</i>

00:34:45.960 --> 00:34:49.873
And I think, you know,
you're extremely witty, and you're wise...

00:34:50.040 --> 00:34:53.555
...and I kind of can't believe
I'm actually gonna say this.

00:34:53.960 --> 00:34:55.837
But...

00:34:56.000 --> 00:34:58.389
...actually, I think
we should be friends.

00:34:58.560 --> 00:35:01.632
And I want you to have this.

00:35:01.800 --> 00:35:03.279
I don't wanna be your friend.

00:35:07.120 --> 00:35:08.997
I don't wanna be your friend.

00:35:16.360 --> 00:35:19.113
You can never have
too many copies of <i>The Goonies</i>.

00:35:33.160 --> 00:35:35.549
That was corporate espionage.
I could've fired you.

00:35:35.720 --> 00:35:37.358
Even sued you for breach
of confidentiality.

00:35:37.520 --> 00:35:41.274
Dad. You were extorting the county,
putting the company at huge risks.

00:35:41.440 --> 00:35:43.431
One day this was gonna come out.
Then what?

00:35:43.600 --> 00:35:47.673
When you found that report,
you could've shown me.

00:35:47.840 --> 00:35:49.831
You could've shown me
when it started.

00:35:50.000 --> 00:35:52.070
I'm sorry, but I just didn't see
any other way.

00:35:52.240 --> 00:35:57.519
It was dishonest,
calculating and ruthless. Kiki...

00:35:57.840 --> 00:36:00.308
...we just might make
a real-estate mogul out of you yet.

00:36:02.160 --> 00:36:04.071
Well, that's something to look forward to.

00:36:08.240 --> 00:36:11.118
Your mom's ornaments.
The tree looks nice.

00:36:12.400 --> 00:36:14.960
There may be a gift under there for you.

00:36:15.640 --> 00:36:17.039
Maybe.

00:36:18.680 --> 00:36:21.911
Hey, where you going?
We were thinking about getting a movie.

00:36:22.080 --> 00:36:23.911
Marissa's going to see her therapist.

00:36:24.080 --> 00:36:26.958
- She's going through a lot.
- Yeah, I thought I'd go with her.

00:36:27.720 --> 00:36:29.631
Yeah, you could...

00:36:29.800 --> 00:36:31.756
...or not.

00:36:33.480 --> 00:36:38.031
Marissa's gonna have to figure this
out by herself, and you gotta let her.

00:36:39.040 --> 00:36:41.998
You're here with us now.
You don't have to be the parent anymore.

00:36:45.560 --> 00:36:48.472
- A movie, huh?
- Yeah, but it's my pick.

00:36:48.640 --> 00:36:51.518
The selection of a movie
is something of an art.

00:37:29.040 --> 00:37:32.794
I came here three times before I
actually walked through that door.

00:37:36.400 --> 00:37:39.312
I know you. You go to Harbor, right?

00:37:40.120 --> 00:37:42.111
Marissa Cooper. Hi.

00:37:42.480 --> 00:37:46.996
You're the girl at school who
organizes things. Parties and stuff, right?

00:37:47.800 --> 00:37:50.030
Social chair is what that's called.

00:37:57.200 --> 00:38:01.239
- You go to Harbor?
- No. No, I go to Pacific.

00:38:01.560 --> 00:38:03.073
Oliver Trask.

00:38:06.560 --> 00:38:11.509
For a social chair... Well, I don't
find you to be very social at all.

00:38:11.680 --> 00:38:14.717
Gonna have to talk
to somebody about a recall.

00:38:14.880 --> 00:38:19.431
This is a psychiatrist's office.
It's kind of embarrassing.

00:38:19.600 --> 00:38:23.878
Yeah. Yeah, you're right.
This is totally embarrassing.

00:38:24.480 --> 00:38:27.677
So let's address the obvious and move on.

00:38:28.480 --> 00:38:30.630
What's wrong with you?

00:38:35.160 --> 00:38:37.674
What is wrong with you?

00:38:39.120 --> 00:38:41.634
Well, if I knew, I wouldn't be here.

00:38:44.640 --> 00:38:47.234
You're not an alcoholic yet.

00:38:47.400 --> 00:38:48.799
You've OD'd at least once.

00:38:49.400 --> 00:38:52.949
Pills, I'd say.
Muscle relaxants, definitely.

00:38:57.520 --> 00:38:58.873
Painkillers.

00:39:00.080 --> 00:39:01.991
You didn't really want to hurt yourself.

00:39:02.160 --> 00:39:05.038
Kurt Cobain, yeah,
he wanted to hurt himself.

00:39:07.920 --> 00:39:10.036
You know, coming here wasn't my idea.

00:39:10.720 --> 00:39:14.554
Maybe not. But you wouldn't be here
if you didn't want to be.

00:39:15.720 --> 00:39:18.234
You want to know
why you are the way you are.

00:39:22.680 --> 00:39:25.399
That's you. I'm waiting on the next door.

00:39:27.560 --> 00:39:29.437
See you next week.

00:39:40.240 --> 00:39:42.196
How did it go with the girls?

00:39:42.360 --> 00:39:45.875
- Seth Cohen starter pack?
- I think I'm past that now.

00:39:48.400 --> 00:39:50.789
- Is that what I think it is?
- Figured I'd hang it.

00:39:51.280 --> 00:39:54.397
All right, man,
another Chrismukkah convert.

00:39:54.560 --> 00:39:55.549
Nice.

00:39:55.720 --> 00:39:59.998
I never doubted it for a second. Check it
out, I already put the hook up just in case.

00:40:02.040 --> 00:40:04.793
- Hey.
- All right, what'll it be?

00:40:04.960 --> 00:40:07.155
<i>Fiddler on the Roof,</i>
<i>It's a Wonderful Life...</i>

00:40:07.320 --> 00:40:10.039
...or my selection,
Sylvester Stallone's <i>Over the Top.</i>

00:40:10.200 --> 00:40:13.909
- Isn't that the arm-wrestling movie?
- Arm-wrestling classic.

00:40:14.080 --> 00:40:19.200
- Hey, merry Chrismukkah, you guys.
- Thank you.

00:00:0.500 --> 00:00:2.00
